result.adr_address: 63 Nathan Rd, Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 63 Nathan Rd, Tsim Sha Tsui, Hong Kong
result.name: Champ Kitchen

reviews.text:
Actually this restaurant is western style but this time we arranged a fusion menu with mainly Chinese style.

In fact it share the same kitchen with the neighbour Chinese restaurant as they belong to the same group.

For Chinese style we had abalone tart, conch soup, crispy chicken and fried rice.

For Western style we had salad, truffle scallop, grilled tenderloin and flounder.

I like the Chinese style more personally. Overall delicious food with high quality. But at this price it is what you expected, or some may expect more.

Good environment with live band at dinner time.

By the way the fusion menu is by request only.

Came for a high tea set offered as an Asia miles reward benefit. Sad to say it was particularly disappointing on all counts. Unable to cater to vegetarians, inflexible management policies impacts customer service. Only 2 types of tea offered. Average cakes served, and be sure to remind staff to bring tea with your TEA set. Not a scone in sight for miles. First world problems, but there's much better places for afternoon tea. Don't waste your Asia miles on this place.
Nice view, good service, average Western cuisine standard.
Freshly made delicious High Tea set and prompt service ;)

Food was really plain, service was below average but the view was great. Didn't have half of the dishes we ordered and the paella and ribs were so flavorless - giving 'western food' a bad rep. Clearly didn't know how to cook 'western food'. The view was amazing such a shame the food was so expensive and plain. Service was not great. I was asking about a dim sum dish which I had there last time and wasn't on the menu. Then waiter wasn't very nice and insisted that dim sum was only for lunch. But then I found it on their specials card - oh I guess you do serve dim sum...

reviews.text:
A restaurant in Tsim Sha Tsui with firework views. Highly recommend for dinner events.
Food is gorgeous!
Large portions, and the food was very good. I suggest going with a group, makes it easier to share family-style. Great views if you are lucky enough to sit by the windows.

They claim to serve the best steaks. I ordered a 12 ounce Prime Certified Angus Beef Ribeye but was totally disappointed when the steak I requested to be medium rare turned up medium done. The quality of the steak is far from the level of USDA Prime. (The restaurant claimed that the quality of the CAB prime beef was even better than that of USDA Prime. I highly doubt their claim from my experience here.) The table setting was almost bare to the extent that you wouldn't be able to tell between this restaurant and any roadside tea house in Hong Kong. The only saving grace was the view of Hong Kong Island which was awesome.
We had the semi lunch buffet and was really good, it was a Friday but very quiet. Fantastic view and good service! Friends had steak and I had fish, all very nice!
Very nice atmosphere, food ok

reviews.text: Isquare  Is a nice shopping mall it has really call art work in front of it. It's really busy has a lot of nice shops that are all open past 10:00 p.m. It's in a convenient location from the Subway. Has some good restaurants in it. And the movie theater

It's a modern and great design shopping center and close to my hotel. I went here for a lunch and found Mark & Spencer on the ground floor and shopped a bit here. Overall, it's a nice shopping center.
Good for shopping (M&S clothing and food hall, marketplace), kids-r-us and other kid brands, very good cinema, linked to TST MTR train station
Visited the EyeLounge.  Very nice location with breath taking views of the city! Good drinks and very nice restaurant and cuisine.
High end shopping mall in Kowloon. Big brands.
